value.0: This boatman used to be a raft operator, until he was attacked by a Drow patrol boat. Now he operates a Drow patrol boat and only wears the finest Drow armour.

A diabolical crossbow; with each pull of the trigger a flaming bolt springs forth, easily burning through the flesh of a foe. Used commonly by assassins, it enchances the wearers sight of hearing and vision, while being sturdy built enough to give it extreme precision and might.

Dogma of Faluzure: Faluzure teaches that, as long as the lives of dragons are, still they are finite. This need not be the case, however, for undeath lies beyond like a tantalizing treasure trove. Most believe that Faluzure played a part in the creation of the first undead dragons, though he is not mentioned in the legend of Dragotha.
You can take a tiny chip of this crystal and use it as a lens in your porting wand.
